isDeterministic

public static boolean isDeterministic(FSAModel model)
Determines whether the model is deterministic, i.e. contains no epsilon transitions, has no more than one initial state (but could have none), and from each state there is not more than one transition with a given event.

Parameters:
model - the model to be checked
Returns:
false if model contains epsilon transitions, has more than one initial state or has a state with more than one transition firing on the same event, true otherwise.

hasControllabilityConflict

public static boolean hasControllabilityConflict(FSAModel[] models)
A check to see whether there is a conflict in the controllability attribute of events contained in the given models.

Parameters:
models - the models containing the events whose controllability attributes have to be checked for conflict
Returns:
true if an event with the same name exists in any pair of models but is controllable in one and uncontrollable in the other, false otherwise.

hasObservabilityConflict

public static boolean hasObservabilityConflict(FSAModel[] models)
A check to see whether there is a conflict in the observability attribute of events contained in the given models.

Parameters:
models - the models containing the events whose observability attributes have to be checked for conflict
Returns:
true if an event with the same name exists in any pair of models but is observable in one and unobservable in the other, false otherwise.
